WEBVTT

00:03.420 --> 00:05.960
Katie: Making breakfast
for your kid with OCD

00:05.960 --> 00:09.040
is like the world's least-fun
game of "Operation."

00:09.040 --> 00:11.290
It takes a steady hand or --

00:11.290 --> 00:12.330
[ Imitates buzzer ]

00:12.330 --> 00:14.250
It touched.
I can't eat that.

00:14.250 --> 00:16.790
If we were rich, Anna-Kat
would be eccentric.

00:16.790 --> 00:19.080
But we're poor, so she's just
cuckoo pants.

00:19.080 --> 00:20.250
Call me when you
get it right.

00:23.500 --> 00:25.120
Morning, Taylor.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.580
I made you a little
something.

00:26.580 --> 00:28.580
No, way. I'm not eating
Anna-Kat's reject food.

00:28.580 --> 00:29.540
It's disgusting.

00:29.540 --> 00:31.710
Mmm! Yolks and crusties.
May I?

00:31.710 --> 00:33.290
Put that cup down!

00:33.290 --> 00:35.120
Who gave you permission
to drink coffee?

00:35.120 --> 00:36.380
You did last week.

00:36.380 --> 00:38.080
I asked you when
you were removing

00:38.080 --> 00:40.040
all the things Anna-Kat
hates from her trail mix.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.500
Mmm! Carob.
You know better than

00:41.500 --> 00:43.080
to listen to me while
I'm ignoring you.

00:43.080 --> 00:46.120
Besides, coffee stunts
your growth.
Great.

00:46.120 --> 00:47.500
I'm already at
a perfect height

00:47.500 --> 00:49.210
according to the quiz
I took on BuzzFeed.

00:49.210 --> 00:50.670
Well, BuzzFeed says
that I'm a Charlotte,

00:50.670 --> 00:53.080
which is total crap 'cause
everyone knows I'm a Carrie.

00:53.080 --> 00:54.540
You're more like
a Miranda.

00:54.540 --> 00:56.710
That is the meanest thing
anyone's ever said to me.

00:56.710 --> 00:57.750
Not happening.

00:57.750 --> 00:58.620
Put it down.

00:58.620 --> 01:00.670
Fine.

01:00.670 --> 01:03.250
Once I start driving next week,
I'll go get my own coffee.

01:06.920 --> 01:08.500
Oh, my God.
She's right.

01:08.500 --> 01:11.250
She's gonna be driving.
How did this happen?

01:11.250 --> 01:14.210
When did our oldest
get to be so old?
I don't understand.

01:14.210 --> 01:16.080
I thought you couldn't wait
for Taylor to start driving.

01:16.080 --> 01:18.210
Well, now that it's here,
I'm having mixed feelings.

01:20.210 --> 01:22.170
Am I allowed to have those,
Greg, or is this Russia?

01:22.170 --> 01:23.380
Do you mean
Communist Russia?

01:23.380 --> 01:25.080
Because modern Russia,
while still oppressive --

01:25.080 --> 01:26.880
Why can't you just
let me say things?

01:26.880 --> 01:30.380
Greg, you realize getting her
license means independence.

01:30.380 --> 01:32.330
And before you know it,
she's gonna be driving off

01:32.330 --> 01:34.380
like that girl in that
Subaru commercial.

01:34.380 --> 01:35.710
You mean the one where
the little girl sits

01:35.710 --> 01:37.750
in the driver's seat and
the dad tells her to be careful?

01:37.750 --> 01:38.790
[ Voice breaking ]
Then he turns back,

01:38.790 --> 01:40.460
and suddenly
she's a teenager.

01:40.460 --> 01:42.330
[ Voice breaking ]
That girl was so tiny.

01:42.330 --> 01:45.500
Then the girl grew up
right before his eyes.

01:45.500 --> 01:47.500
[ Both sniffling ]

01:47.500 --> 01:48.620
Oh.

01:50.710 --> 01:51.670
What's happening?

01:57.170 --> 01:58.790
Ugh. Get off.

01:58.790 --> 02:00.620
Taylor, honey,
I'd like to spend

02:00.620 --> 02:02.540
some special mother/daughter
time with you,

02:02.540 --> 02:04.880
establish a bond that
will last a lifetime.

02:04.880 --> 02:06.380
You can't force
stuff like that.

02:06.380 --> 02:08.040
That's silly.
Anything can be forced.

02:08.040 --> 02:09.710
The fact that you were
all over 9 pounds

02:09.710 --> 02:11.290
and I never had
a C-section is proof.

02:11.290 --> 02:13.040
Gross.
Yes, it was.

02:13.040 --> 02:14.000
I saw the sheets.
Mm-hmm.

02:15.750 --> 02:17.960
You'll never believe who just
moved in next to us.

02:17.960 --> 02:19.960
Here's a hint --
He's one of my idols,

02:19.960 --> 02:20.960
and he just got
out of prison.

02:20.960 --> 02:22.460
I give up...

02:22.460 --> 02:24.540
on the question
and possibly parenting.

02:24.540 --> 02:26.170
Spencer Blitz, the man
who dominated

02:26.170 --> 02:27.380
Wall Street
in the '90s.

02:27.380 --> 02:29.040
Then spent the last
20 years in jail

02:29.040 --> 02:30.460
for insider trading.

02:30.460 --> 02:31.880
I want you to stay clear
of that guy.

02:33.210 --> 02:34.540
You've already talked to him,
haven't you?

02:36.580 --> 02:37.750
Spencer: Hey.

02:37.750 --> 02:40.040
Are you stealing
my Wall Street Journal?

02:41.620 --> 02:42.880
Good job.

02:42.880 --> 02:45.500
When I was your age,
I stole hundreds of papers.

02:45.500 --> 02:47.330
Sold 'em back to
the vendors for a profit.

02:47.330 --> 02:49.040
Kind of a reverse
paper route.

02:49.040 --> 02:51.580
Then I took that money,
bought an abandoned warehouse,

02:51.580 --> 02:53.210
burned it to the ground
for the insurance money,

02:53.210 --> 02:54.920
and bought
a Maserati.

02:54.920 --> 02:56.750
At school, I made sure
I parked

02:56.750 --> 02:59.620
next the the principal
so he knew who was boss.

02:59.620 --> 03:02.040
Sir, that's the most inspiring
story I've ever heard.

03:02.040 --> 03:03.500
[ Chuckles ]

03:03.500 --> 03:05.330
That guy's a perfect example
of what happens

03:05.330 --> 03:06.830
when somebody only cares
about money.

03:06.830 --> 03:08.000
I know, right?

03:08.000 --> 03:09.250
He's the best.

03:12.500 --> 03:15.750
Oliver, there is a letter from
your school marked "urgent."

03:15.750 --> 03:17.380
Oh, yeah, I was supposed
to give that to you.

03:17.380 --> 03:19.500
Yeah, I got that, too.
So did Anna-Kat.

03:19.500 --> 03:21.960
You know I hate it when the
three of you screw up together.

03:21.960 --> 03:23.210
It dilutes her anger.

03:23.210 --> 03:25.540
A kid at the school
got lice,

03:25.540 --> 03:27.670
and they want the parents
to be on the lookout.

03:27.670 --> 03:28.710
[ Pig grunting ]

03:28.710 --> 03:30.460
We cannot get lice.

03:30.460 --> 03:32.170
We're already known
as the poor family.

03:33.540 --> 03:34.670
[ Pig sneezes ]

03:34.670 --> 03:37.500
Correction -- poor family
with a pet pig.

03:37.500 --> 03:39.290
Hans Gruber, don't sneeze
on Mommy's leg.

03:39.290 --> 03:42.580
Greg, don't ever refer to me
as the pig's mommy again.

03:42.580 --> 03:43.830
Listen up.

03:43.830 --> 03:45.960
We will not be known as
the "poor pig family

03:45.960 --> 03:48.670
that also has lice."

03:48.670 --> 03:51.670
So that's what
these things are.

03:57.920 --> 04:00.040
After discovering that
one of your kids has lice,

04:00.040 --> 04:02.880
the first step is to isolate
patient zero.

04:02.880 --> 04:04.420
This is to contain them.

04:04.420 --> 04:06.580
Having head pets
is the best.

04:06.580 --> 04:09.580
Really? But eggs
touching toast is gross?

04:09.580 --> 04:11.000
That is one wavy line.

04:12.790 --> 04:15.500
Step two, check all remaining
family members.

04:15.500 --> 04:16.750
You're good.

04:18.330 --> 04:19.290
You, too.

04:22.380 --> 04:23.500
All clear.

04:23.500 --> 04:25.210
Mmm.

04:25.210 --> 04:26.790
Did you just moan
during a lice check?

04:26.790 --> 04:28.120
If you're into it, yeah.

04:29.750 --> 04:32.420
Step three is to kill
those little bastards --

04:32.420 --> 04:33.790
the lice, not the kids.

04:33.790 --> 04:35.040
Maybe the kids.

04:35.040 --> 04:37.000
It's like
there's a village.

04:37.000 --> 04:39.250
You'd have to get lice
for a very long time

04:39.250 --> 04:41.120
to have as many
as I do.

04:41.120 --> 04:43.080
I've got a super swarm.

04:43.080 --> 04:44.000
Ugh.

04:47.210 --> 04:48.750
[ Sighs ]

04:48.750 --> 04:50.040
Step four,

04:50.040 --> 04:52.290
shock and awe.

04:52.290 --> 04:53.620
[ Exhales deeply ]

04:53.620 --> 04:56.670
Lice get everywhere
and on everything.

04:56.670 --> 04:58.330
They're the glitter
of the bug world.

04:58.330 --> 05:07.500
♪♪

05:07.500 --> 05:09.250
I'm going to
Melanie's house.
Wait.

05:09.250 --> 05:10.830
I was hoping that
we could bond.

05:10.830 --> 05:12.500
We'll never get
this time back

05:12.500 --> 05:14.000
or be able to make
these memories again.

05:14.000 --> 05:15.380
Nah, that's okay.

05:15.380 --> 05:16.880
C'mon, we can make
a batch of cookies,

05:16.880 --> 05:18.830
but instead of baking them,
we'll just eat the cookie dough.

05:18.830 --> 05:20.500
You can't eat raw eggs.
You'll get sick.

05:20.500 --> 05:22.080
What is wrong with
your generation?

05:22.080 --> 05:24.500
You won't eat raw eggs
or put plastic in the microwave.

05:24.500 --> 05:26.460
Yeah, we also don't like
to get lice.

05:26.460 --> 05:28.620
Listen, when things get tough
for this family, we don't run.

05:28.620 --> 05:30.880
We stick it out together
under one roof.

05:30.880 --> 05:31.670
Oh, really?

05:31.670 --> 05:32.880
Mm-hmm.

05:32.880 --> 05:35.750
Hmm.

05:35.750 --> 05:37.000
Tell that to Dad.

05:41.750 --> 05:43.210
What a total [bleep]

05:44.380 --> 05:45.790
I love your father.

05:45.790 --> 05:49.120
♪♪

05:49.120 --> 05:51.790
What do you think
you're doing?

05:51.790 --> 05:53.750
During the State of the Union,
a "designated survivor"

05:53.750 --> 05:55.210
is sent to
an undisclosed location

05:55.210 --> 05:56.540
so they can
lead the country

05:56.540 --> 05:58.330
in the event everyone
is wiped out in an attack.

05:58.330 --> 06:00.710
This is exactly like that,
except with lice.

06:00.710 --> 06:01.710
And a tent.

06:01.710 --> 06:03.120
With Nutter Butters.

06:03.120 --> 06:05.330
How can I convince Taylor
to stay and bond with me

06:05.330 --> 06:06.750
if you're out here
pitching a tent?

06:06.750 --> 06:08.580
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, grow up, Greg.

06:08.580 --> 06:10.460
Hey, if lice get in these locks,
they're not getting out.

06:10.460 --> 06:11.460
Remember when --
Yeah, yeah,

06:11.460 --> 06:12.830
Paul Mitchell stopped you
on the street

06:12.830 --> 06:15.040
and told you he had never seen
such texture and definition.

06:15.040 --> 06:16.250
It was texture
and volume.

06:16.250 --> 06:18.040
I only have
a two-week window

06:18.040 --> 06:19.500
to get in all
the bonding time I can,

06:19.500 --> 06:21.500
because, when she gets
her license, she's gone.

06:21.500 --> 06:22.790
And you know how
I know that?

06:22.790 --> 06:24.000
Because that's
what I did.

06:24.000 --> 06:25.750
I got my license,
got a job,

06:25.750 --> 06:27.620
and then quit to follow
Prince and the Evolution.

06:27.620 --> 06:29.620
Don't you mean
Revolution?
No. Evolution.

06:29.620 --> 06:32.790
They were a Prince knock-off
band that owned the Panhandle.

06:32.790 --> 06:35.080
[ Sighs ]
What am I going to do?

06:35.080 --> 06:37.330
Hey, remember the coupon book
she gave you for Mother's Day?

06:37.330 --> 06:38.290
Yes.

06:38.290 --> 06:40.040
With all those
cute activities.

06:40.040 --> 06:41.250
Such a sweet gesture.

06:41.250 --> 06:43.080
It's one of my most treasured
possessions.

06:43.080 --> 06:44.830
Yeah, I saw it smushed up in
the back of the junk drawer.

06:44.830 --> 06:46.290
You bond with Taylor.

06:46.290 --> 06:48.120
I'll do some father/son bonding
out here with Oliver.

06:48.120 --> 06:49.880
Where is he?
He said he'd
be right back.

06:49.880 --> 06:51.880
Hopefully some camping with
his old man will help him

06:51.880 --> 06:54.080
realize there's more to life
than material pursuits.

06:55.500 --> 06:56.960
Oliver: Wow!

06:56.960 --> 06:59.540
This is your TV nook?
[ Laughs ]

06:59.540 --> 07:02.210
You know, every time I try
to find the main TV room,

07:02.210 --> 07:05.380
I end up in
the bowling alley.

07:05.380 --> 07:06.290
So, you haven't
touched this place

07:06.290 --> 07:07.670
since you got arrested
in the '90s?

07:07.670 --> 07:10.290
[ Laughs ]

07:10.290 --> 07:11.380
Who's TLC?

07:11.380 --> 07:12.920
A rad girl band.

07:12.920 --> 07:15.790
They actually played my birthday
just before I was arrested.

07:15.790 --> 07:18.580
I told "Left Eye" the story of
how I torched that warehouse.

07:18.580 --> 07:21.120
Looking back, I worry
I planted a seed.

07:21.120 --> 07:23.210
Is it true you dated
Daryl Hannah?

07:23.210 --> 07:24.960
Post-"Splash,"
pre-"Wall Street."

07:24.960 --> 07:27.580
Undeniably her
sweet spot.

07:27.580 --> 07:29.620
But my heart belonged
to someone else --

07:29.620 --> 07:31.380
a man, in fact...

07:31.380 --> 07:33.380
by the name of
Benjamin Franklin.

07:33.380 --> 07:35.580
I still get goose bumps
every time I look at that

07:35.580 --> 07:37.540
beautiful bald,
green head.

07:37.540 --> 07:40.250
Wow. We have the same
taste in men.

07:40.250 --> 07:43.420
I'm gonna give you some advice
on how to get rich.

07:43.420 --> 07:45.880
Money needs to
be your first,

07:45.880 --> 07:48.620
your second,
and your third love.

07:48.620 --> 07:51.500
Fourth can be a Russian model
who needs a visa.

07:51.500 --> 07:53.380
Do you have, like, a pen
and paper or something?

07:53.380 --> 07:55.290
Yeah.
[ Doorbell rings ]

07:55.290 --> 07:57.620
That's probably
my parole officer.

07:57.620 --> 07:59.120
Coming!

08:03.290 --> 08:04.790
Hi.
You must be Spencer Blitz.

08:04.790 --> 08:05.960
Of course I am.

08:05.960 --> 08:07.290
I'm Greg Otto
from next door.

08:07.290 --> 08:08.250
I was looking for
my son, Oliver.

08:08.250 --> 08:09.460
Come on in.

08:09.460 --> 08:10.380
Thank you.

08:12.920 --> 08:14.750
Hey, Dad.

08:14.750 --> 08:17.000
Spencer was just telling me
a story about how he manipulated

08:17.000 --> 08:19.330
the Malaysian housing market
for a huge profit.

08:19.330 --> 08:21.210
You got one hell
of a son here.

08:21.210 --> 08:22.540
I look at him, and I see

08:22.540 --> 08:25.330
a younger, less-tan version
of myself.

08:25.330 --> 08:27.080
I hope one day I can
follow in your footsteps.

08:27.080 --> 08:29.250
But not to jail.
Am I right?

08:29.250 --> 08:31.290
Yeah, well, federal
prison's not so bad.

08:31.290 --> 08:33.040
He told me Allenwood
had a golf course.

08:33.040 --> 08:34.330
That's where I spent
the summer.

08:34.330 --> 08:36.620
I winter-prisoned
in Arizona.
Amazing.

08:36.620 --> 08:38.040
But it wasn't worth it,
because he had

08:38.040 --> 08:39.000
to give back
all that money

08:39.000 --> 08:40.120
when he was caught
stealing.

08:40.120 --> 08:41.710
Well, what your dad
says is true.

08:41.710 --> 08:43.790
I'm down to my last several
hundred million.

08:43.790 --> 08:45.460
It's tough to look at
those statements.

08:45.460 --> 08:47.250
Okay, we'd love to
stay and talk,

08:47.250 --> 08:48.750
but Oliver and I
have to get going.

08:48.750 --> 08:49.880
We do?

08:49.880 --> 08:51.040
We're doing some
backyard camping.

08:51.040 --> 08:52.830
Yeah, but --
That sounds nice.

08:52.830 --> 08:54.000
Go with your dad.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.080
You can come
visit me anytime.

08:56.080 --> 08:57.330
You know, I n--
I never had a family.

08:57.330 --> 08:59.210
I was too busy
making money.

08:59.210 --> 09:00.380
And it's hard to live
with regret.

09:00.380 --> 09:01.790
Regret?
Oh, no, sorry,

09:01.790 --> 09:03.290
I had the wrong
inflection.

09:03.290 --> 09:05.830
I never had a family.
I was too busy making money!

09:08.080 --> 09:09.670
Mama?

09:09.670 --> 09:11.960
Will you take the middle out
of my fidget spinner for me?

09:11.960 --> 09:13.710
Didn't you just ask me
to put it back in?

09:13.710 --> 09:14.920
Uh-huh.

09:14.920 --> 09:16.210
[ Sighs ]

09:16.210 --> 09:17.830
I can't find anything
in this junk drawer.

09:19.040 --> 09:20.080
Heads up, honey.

09:23.040 --> 09:25.170
Why do I have to have
my hair in braids?

09:25.170 --> 09:26.920
You have to do it
after you treat for lice.

09:26.920 --> 09:29.210
[ Gasps ]
The coupon book!

09:29.210 --> 09:30.120
Ew.

09:30.120 --> 09:31.830
Stuck to an old
Life Saver.

09:31.830 --> 09:34.830
That I won't eat
until I'm alone.

09:34.830 --> 09:36.080
You keep itching.

09:36.080 --> 09:37.420
Do you have
head pets, too?

09:37.420 --> 09:39.210
No.

09:39.210 --> 09:40.120
Of course not.

09:40.120 --> 09:41.250
[ Chuckles ]

09:41.250 --> 09:42.920
Can you hand me
that fork?

09:45.120 --> 09:47.250
Mamas do this sometimes.

09:47.250 --> 09:51.460
♪♪

09:51.460 --> 09:54.120
Oliver, I know Spencer
has made a lot of money,

09:54.120 --> 09:56.330
but that came at
a huge price.

09:56.330 --> 09:58.540
In life, there are
no shortcuts.

09:58.540 --> 10:01.210
The only way to really make it
is to get a job and work hard.

10:01.210 --> 10:03.620
I actually took a job
this afternoon.
Oh, doing what?

10:03.620 --> 10:06.080
Running errands for Spencer
until he's legally permitted

10:06.080 --> 10:08.210
to step outside a half-mile
radius of his property.

10:08.210 --> 10:09.170
[ Beeper beeps ]

10:09.170 --> 10:10.290
That's him right now.

10:10.290 --> 10:12.080
Is that a beeper?
Isn't it cool?

10:12.080 --> 10:14.290
It's like a cellphone,
only it does nothing.

10:14.290 --> 10:15.880
I've got to roll.
Spencer asked me to get

10:15.880 --> 10:17.620
Crystal Pepsi and something
called mousse.

10:17.620 --> 10:22.920
♪♪

10:22.920 --> 10:24.040
Katie: Where are
you going?
Aah!

10:25.460 --> 10:27.880
I told you,
to Melanie's.
No, you're not.

10:27.880 --> 10:29.120
Because I am redeeming

10:29.120 --> 10:31.210
the Mother's Day coupons
you gave me.

10:31.210 --> 10:32.750
Don't be weird.
I gave those to you

10:32.750 --> 10:34.880
when I was like 10.
I don't see
an expiration date.

10:34.880 --> 10:36.290
[ Gasps ]

10:36.290 --> 10:39.080
Here's one for an ice cream
"zunday"...

10:39.080 --> 10:40.540
[Voice breaking]
spelled with a Z.

10:40.540 --> 10:43.040
I am not hanging out in
a house crawling with bugs.

10:43.040 --> 10:44.380
I have that problem
under control.

10:44.380 --> 10:45.620
Yeah?

10:45.620 --> 10:47.420
Then why do you keep
itching your head?

10:47.420 --> 10:48.290
I'm not itching.

10:48.290 --> 10:51.170
I'm stimulating
the follicles

10:51.170 --> 10:53.500
because of female-pattern
baldness.

10:53.500 --> 10:54.620
It's coming for you, too.

10:55.670 --> 10:56.830
Oh, my God.

10:56.830 --> 10:58.210
The top of my head
is just lice

10:58.210 --> 10:59.580
with some hair
around it.

10:59.580 --> 11:00.580
You can't make me
hang out

11:00.580 --> 11:02.330
in a lice-infested
house.

11:02.330 --> 11:03.580
You're losing her, Katie.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.500
Do something.

11:05.500 --> 11:07.880
Taylor, wait!

11:07.880 --> 11:08.790
Should I?

11:08.790 --> 11:10.080
No.

11:10.080 --> 11:11.420
And yet I'm doing it.

11:11.420 --> 11:12.880
Lice hat!

11:12.880 --> 11:14.500
Now we're infested
together.

11:14.500 --> 11:16.830
Oh, my God!
Have you gone insane?!

11:16.830 --> 11:20.250
I will take my 10 free hugs
inside, please.

11:20.580 --> 11:22.120
♪♪

11:26.460 --> 11:28.000
What's it like
on the inside?

11:28.000 --> 11:29.290
Taylor totally
ignored me

11:29.290 --> 11:31.040
while I was combing lice
out of her hair.

11:31.040 --> 11:32.880
Now she's holed up in her room
and won't come out.

11:32.880 --> 11:35.000
Huh. Weird.

11:35.000 --> 11:36.330
I guess you could try
giving her bedbugs.

11:36.330 --> 11:38.380
It was a spur-of-the-moment
decision.

11:38.380 --> 11:39.920
Besides, Oliver
has become a runner

11:39.920 --> 11:41.420
for a criminal
on your watch.

11:41.420 --> 11:42.830
Okay, we've both
made mistakes.

11:42.830 --> 11:44.920
Am I crazy for trying
to force Taylor

11:44.920 --> 11:45.830
to spend
mother/daughter time?

11:45.830 --> 11:47.420
No, I get it.

11:47.420 --> 11:49.620
You're just anxious because,
before you know it...

11:49.620 --> 11:51.330
Subaru commercial.
...Subaru commercial.

11:54.960 --> 11:57.000
Okay.

11:57.000 --> 11:59.290
How are you gonna handle
the Oliver situation?

11:59.290 --> 12:01.120
Well, if I forbid him
from seeing Spencer,

12:01.120 --> 12:02.580
it's just gonna make him
want to go over there more,

12:02.580 --> 12:03.880
so I'm gonna have
a chat with Spencer

12:03.880 --> 12:05.170
and set some
ground rules.

12:05.170 --> 12:06.380
What's your move
with Taylor?

12:06.380 --> 12:08.420
I'm gonna go get some advice
from Angela and Doris.

12:08.420 --> 12:10.670
So if it goes wrong,
I can blame them.

12:10.670 --> 12:11.880
It's nice to see
I'm not the only one

12:11.880 --> 12:12.750
you use that
technique on.

12:12.750 --> 12:14.790
Yeah, but don't worry.

12:14.790 --> 12:16.790
You'll always be my favorite
person to blame.

12:16.790 --> 12:17.880
That's sweet.

12:17.880 --> 12:24.000
♪♪

12:24.000 --> 12:25.290
I don't know what to do.

12:25.290 --> 12:26.580
Taylor grew up overnight

12:26.580 --> 12:27.920
and doesn't want to
spend time with me,

12:27.920 --> 12:29.460
and Anna-Kat
gave me lice.

12:29.460 --> 12:30.750
You have lice?!

12:30.750 --> 12:32.710
[ Gasps ]
Lice braids!

12:32.710 --> 12:35.460
Had lice -- past tense.
Combed 'em all out.

12:35.460 --> 12:37.080
Combing doesn't always
work the first time.

12:37.080 --> 12:38.460
I can't believe
you hugged me.

12:38.460 --> 12:40.710
So what?! I'm supposed to
not go to restaurants

12:40.710 --> 12:42.290
and hug my friends
when I have lice?

12:42.290 --> 12:43.750
Uh, yes.

12:43.750 --> 12:45.040
Doris, say something.

12:46.540 --> 12:47.790
I'm three months
pregnant.

12:47.790 --> 12:49.210
What?
What?

12:49.210 --> 12:50.540
So I also have
a parasite

12:50.540 --> 12:52.330
sucking the nutrients
out of my body.

12:52.330 --> 12:53.920
How did that happen?

12:53.920 --> 12:55.830
I was in bed
guzzling Chardonnay

12:55.830 --> 12:57.670
and watching Michael Phelps
race a shark.

12:57.670 --> 12:59.960
Then I got so worked up
that I jumped Richard

12:59.960 --> 13:01.460
like it was the 17th
of the month!

13:02.880 --> 13:04.790
That's our bone day.

13:04.790 --> 13:06.120
Oh, my God.

13:06.120 --> 13:07.790
How are you feeling?
Pissed!

13:07.790 --> 13:09.540
Pissed that I'm about to
have my fourth child!

13:09.540 --> 13:11.920
I had eight years until my
youngest left for Princeton --

13:11.920 --> 13:14.290
September 10, 2025.

13:14.290 --> 13:16.170
Then I would jet off
to Majorca,

13:16.170 --> 13:17.920
find a little villa
on a cliff,

13:17.920 --> 13:19.210
learn to sculpt,

13:19.210 --> 13:20.290
maybe take a lover --

13:20.290 --> 13:22.040
possibly my sculpting
teacher.

13:22.040 --> 13:24.120
Now this little creature
moved my finish line.

13:24.120 --> 13:25.420
By the time I get
to Majorca,

13:25.420 --> 13:27.750
I'm gonna be so old that
my sculpting teacher

13:27.750 --> 13:29.750
is gonna rebuff
my aggressive advances.

13:29.750 --> 13:31.460
Look, I come
from a place

13:31.460 --> 13:33.250
where everything happens
for a reason.

13:33.250 --> 13:34.920
This may not be
part of your plan,

13:34.920 --> 13:36.830
but it's obviously part
of the universe's plan.

13:36.830 --> 13:38.710
Oh! I see.

13:38.710 --> 13:41.460
So if I poke you hard
with this fork,

13:41.460 --> 13:44.210
is that also part of
the universe's plan?

13:44.210 --> 13:46.080
Is it, Angela?!
Don't be mad at me.

13:46.080 --> 13:48.170
I'm not the one who uses
"rarely having sex"

13:48.170 --> 13:49.620
as a form of
birth control.

13:49.620 --> 13:52.000
Should I have another baby,
get a fresh start?

13:52.000 --> 13:54.290
Are you crazy?!
I'm not having a baby.

13:54.290 --> 13:57.000
I have to figure out a way to
get closer to the one I have.

13:57.000 --> 13:58.580
They're looking at you.

13:58.580 --> 13:59.880
Say something.

13:59.880 --> 14:01.750
Diaphragm.
Exactly.

14:01.750 --> 14:03.880
Whew! I got lucky
on that one.

14:03.880 --> 14:05.750
What else was in
that coupon book?

14:05.750 --> 14:08.000
What am I gonna do,
pillow fight?

14:08.000 --> 14:09.960
I could come up with something
better than that.

14:11.330 --> 14:12.290
Pillow fight!

14:12.290 --> 14:13.710
What the hell
are you doing?

14:13.710 --> 14:15.960
Having the time
of our lives!

14:15.960 --> 14:18.250
I could hit you all day.

14:18.250 --> 14:21.000
I lied.
That's exhausting.

14:21.000 --> 14:22.580
Ugh.

14:22.580 --> 14:25.000
No wonder sorority girls
are in such good shape.

14:25.000 --> 14:27.210
Are we done?
Look, I'm sorry.

14:27.210 --> 14:29.210
I just want
to spend time with you.

14:29.210 --> 14:31.420
That's why I broke out
the old coupon book you gave me.

14:31.420 --> 14:33.420
Why didn't you just use them
when I gave them to you?

14:35.960 --> 14:37.710
I don't actually know.

14:37.710 --> 14:40.920
Anna-Kat: Mama! Will you squeeze
the toothpaste on my toothbrush?

14:40.920 --> 14:42.380
Sure, honey!

14:42.380 --> 14:44.580
Just so you know,
that's why.

14:44.580 --> 14:45.920
What's that supposed
to mean?

14:45.920 --> 14:47.040
You never used
them because

14:47.040 --> 14:48.920
you were always so distracted
by Anna-Kat.

14:48.920 --> 14:50.580
I mean, I get it.

14:50.580 --> 14:53.580
She's had issues --
has issues.

14:53.580 --> 14:55.210
But she's eight now.

14:55.210 --> 14:56.540
She can put on
her own toothpaste

14:56.540 --> 14:57.750
and take the crust off
her toast.

14:57.750 --> 14:59.250
I've seen her do it.

14:59.250 --> 15:00.420
Have you seen her
put the center

15:00.420 --> 15:01.620
back in the fidget
spinner?

15:01.620 --> 15:03.670
Only about
a million times.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.080
Anna-Kat.

15:07.330 --> 15:10.750
Taylor, honey,
I feel terrible.

15:10.750 --> 15:12.080
Tell you what.

15:12.080 --> 15:16.210
I will let you have
one free hit.

15:18.210 --> 15:19.670
Never let your
guard down!

15:19.670 --> 15:26.380
♪♪

15:26.380 --> 15:27.540
Oh, hey, Greg.

15:27.540 --> 15:29.040
I was expecting Oliver.

15:29.040 --> 15:30.920
I sent him out
for some lobster.

15:30.920 --> 15:32.750
Got nostalgic
for prison food.

15:32.750 --> 15:34.670
I can't believe my tax dollars
paid for that.

15:34.670 --> 15:35.790
You pay taxes?

15:35.790 --> 15:39.120
[ Laughs ]

15:39.120 --> 15:42.210
Greg, I know why
you're here.

15:42.210 --> 15:45.080
You're afraid I'm going
to corrupt your boy.
Yes.

15:45.080 --> 15:46.750
He looks up to you, and
whether I like it or not,

15:46.750 --> 15:48.330
you're a bit of
a role model to him.

15:48.330 --> 15:50.710
Well, that's -- that's
understandable.

15:50.710 --> 15:52.040
I'd feel the same way
about me

15:52.040 --> 15:54.290
if I had just moved in
next to myself.

15:54.290 --> 15:56.500
I will say, your confidence
is quite intoxicating.

15:56.500 --> 15:58.330
I've been drunk on it
since birth.

16:00.250 --> 16:02.210
You don't want me
hanging around him.

16:02.210 --> 16:05.540
If that's what you want,
I'll respect it.
Thank you.

16:05.540 --> 16:08.250
But you should know he's been
a real great asset to me.

16:08.250 --> 16:10.790
He has?

16:10.790 --> 16:13.380
I'm not used to
showing weakness

16:13.380 --> 16:15.380
because, in business,
it could cost you money.

16:15.380 --> 16:18.500
In prison, well, you end up
with a terrible tee time.

16:18.500 --> 16:20.830
I must admit, I've been
a bit lost since I got out.

16:20.830 --> 16:22.460
Things have changed.

16:22.460 --> 16:24.500
Do you know there's no longer
Blockbuster Video?

16:24.500 --> 16:26.960
Yeah. I miss Gerald's
employee picks.

16:26.960 --> 16:28.580
He and I were really
simpatico.

16:28.580 --> 16:30.540
Oliver's getting me
back up to speed.

16:30.540 --> 16:32.040
He's a really great kid,

16:32.040 --> 16:34.120
and that's because
he has great parents.

16:34.120 --> 16:35.670
I feel like you're
manipulating me.

16:35.670 --> 16:37.920
A little.

16:37.920 --> 16:39.170
So, what's it
gonna take?

16:39.170 --> 16:40.330
What do you mean?

16:40.330 --> 16:42.420
How much to make you
change your mind?

16:42.420 --> 16:44.960
$10,000?

16:44.960 --> 16:47.250
You can't pay me
to hang out with my son.

16:47.250 --> 16:48.880
$1 million.

16:48.880 --> 16:50.920
Seriously?
No.

16:50.920 --> 16:52.250
But now that I know
there's a price,

16:52.250 --> 16:53.330
my lawyer will
be in touch.

16:54.710 --> 16:56.080
Ugh. Okay.

16:57.420 --> 16:59.460
Anna-Kat, chalk down.

16:59.460 --> 17:02.460
The days of me doing everything
for you are over.

17:02.460 --> 17:05.330
New rule -- if you can do it,
you're doing it.

17:05.330 --> 17:06.710
For example,

17:06.710 --> 17:09.290
I know you can put toothpaste
on your own toothbrush.

17:09.290 --> 17:10.330
Taylor!

17:10.330 --> 17:12.710
You can also start
your own banana,

17:12.710 --> 17:15.250
stick a straw in a juice box,
and put on your own tights.

17:15.250 --> 17:16.830
Am I clear?

17:16.830 --> 17:18.500
[ Sighs ] Yes.

17:18.500 --> 17:19.880
Good.

17:19.880 --> 17:20.960
[ Sniffles ]
[ Voice breaking ] Okay, Mama.

17:20.960 --> 17:22.540
[ Sniffles ]

17:22.540 --> 17:24.790
I'll just start doing
everything all by myself.

17:24.790 --> 17:27.000
Nice try, but I know you
can turn on and off

17:27.000 --> 17:28.960
the waterworks
like that.

17:28.960 --> 17:30.170
Oliver!

17:30.170 --> 17:37.620
♪♪

17:37.620 --> 17:38.670
[ Door closes ]

17:40.710 --> 17:43.670
Listen, I no longer want you
hanging out with Spencer.

17:43.670 --> 17:45.380
He's not the type of person
we want you learning from.

17:45.380 --> 17:47.250
Who said anything
about learning?

17:47.250 --> 17:49.000
Dad, Spencer's
an old man.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.290
He's alone and has nobody
in his life.

17:51.290 --> 17:53.380
I'm happy to hang out with him
and run errands.

17:53.380 --> 17:54.620
Oh, so you're looking out
for him?

17:54.620 --> 17:56.120
Yeah, let me finish.

17:56.120 --> 17:58.330
Once I become his confidante
and best friend,

17:58.330 --> 18:00.040
I could also become
his sole heir.

18:00.040 --> 18:01.920
And that might pay off
sooner rather than later,

18:01.920 --> 18:03.830
based on the amount of
aspartame he consumes.

18:03.830 --> 18:06.500
Oliver, I don't
think that --
Spencer has no family.

18:06.500 --> 18:07.750
But you know who does?

18:07.750 --> 18:09.620
You do, big guy.

18:09.620 --> 18:11.460
And it's a great family.

18:11.460 --> 18:14.080
Now, let's do some
backyard camping.

18:14.080 --> 18:16.670
I feel like you're
manipulating me.

18:16.670 --> 18:18.000
A little.

18:18.000 --> 18:22.710
♪♪

18:22.710 --> 18:24.880
I feel like I failed her
as a mom.

18:24.880 --> 18:27.210
Just so you know,
if we never had Anna-Kat,

18:27.210 --> 18:28.420
Taylor would be
telling you

18:28.420 --> 18:29.920
you're smothering her
with attention

18:29.920 --> 18:31.250
and ruining her life.

18:31.250 --> 18:33.290
There's no winning
in parenting.

18:33.290 --> 18:34.580
I'm certainly not winning
with Oliver.

18:34.580 --> 18:35.750
Don't feel bad.

18:35.750 --> 18:37.210
It's just Oliver's nature.

18:37.210 --> 18:38.880
I don't like it.
Neither do I.

18:38.880 --> 18:41.830
We need to treat him
like a dog on a leash.

18:41.830 --> 18:43.420
He's gonna try
sniffing around,

18:43.420 --> 18:44.960
but he needs to feel
the tension of us

18:44.960 --> 18:46.670
always yanking him back.

18:46.670 --> 18:49.080
Maybe we should cut
ourselves more slack.
Yeah.

18:49.080 --> 18:51.580
None of our kids are on drugs
or have face tattoos,

18:51.580 --> 18:54.330
and we've never lost track of
a child for more than two hours.

18:54.330 --> 18:55.960
You put it that way,
we're killing it.

18:55.960 --> 18:58.080
So let's put it that way.

18:58.080 --> 18:59.500
Thanks for making me
feel better.

18:59.500 --> 19:01.080
Anytime.

19:03.250 --> 19:04.580
[ Smooches ]

19:04.580 --> 19:12.540
♪♪

19:12.540 --> 19:15.120
Raw cookie dough
is so good.
Right?

19:15.120 --> 19:17.250
Totally worth playing
diarrhea roulette for this.

19:17.250 --> 19:19.080
[ Both laugh ]

19:19.080 --> 19:21.040
Thank you for talking
to Anna-Kat.

19:21.040 --> 19:23.250
Of course.

19:23.250 --> 19:25.620
I guess I was spending so much
time on your little sister

19:25.620 --> 19:28.330
that our time got lost
in the mix.

19:28.330 --> 19:30.000
I'm so sorry,
sweetie.

19:30.000 --> 19:31.620
I really am.

19:31.620 --> 19:32.920
Thanks, Mom.

19:32.920 --> 19:34.380
If I could do it
all over again,

19:34.380 --> 19:37.170
I would've given you more
attention and fewer bugs.

19:37.170 --> 19:38.250
[ Both laugh ]

19:38.250 --> 19:40.380
Anna-Kat: Mama!

19:40.380 --> 19:41.920
You're a big girl!

19:41.920 --> 19:44.500
I'm sure, whatever it is, you
can figure it out on your own.

19:44.500 --> 19:45.960
Okay!

19:48.000 --> 19:50.750
I don't know what to do
with you little guys.

19:50.750 --> 19:54.290
I can't keep you alive
without a warm human host.

19:57.830 --> 19:59.540
Welcome home.

20:05.830 --> 20:10.620
I got some maternity clothes
for the new mama.

20:10.620 --> 20:12.170
They're really just shirts
I've grown out of.

20:14.000 --> 20:16.210
I'm sorry for giving
you guys lice.

20:16.210 --> 20:17.540
But it could've
been anybody.

20:19.210 --> 20:20.710
All right.

20:22.580 --> 20:24.710
I'm sorry to you, too.

20:24.710 --> 20:26.420
[ Thud ]

20:26.420 --> 20:27.500
Ugh.

20:27.500 --> 20:29.080
♪♪
